evaluation.response:
Anya nodded sympathetically. "I can imagine," she said. "It's hard to sleep when your mind is racing with thoughts and plans. But it's good that you're thinking everything through, that you're considering all the details."

She paused, collecting her thoughts. "You know, sometimes the best way to make sure someone remembers something is to make it personal. To make them feel it in a way that they'll never forget."

The villagers began to murmur among themselves, a sense of excitement and anticipation growing in the room.&#x20;
